Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Calculation of the amplitude associated to Goldstone diagrams with alphabetic \
indices\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.888315861110175*^9, 3.8883159051561947`*^9}, {
  3.8883159887111607`*^9, 3.888316043821027*^9}, {3.888316084808132*^9, 
  3.888316094409692*^9}, {3.9080017355726566`*^9, 3.9080017402516623`*^9}, {
  3.9082509561005807`*^9, 
  3.9082509656258793`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9b3bf2eb-6c99-4ae4-901e-\
23e5fd95b3ea"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The three time integrals are evaluated in two steps. First, one computes \
the integrals over ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["t", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dda5378e-0651-417f-8a5a-768a95aa3985"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["t", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a1cac6de-c26e-4a96-ae1d-a7de9dab50f2"],
 " (dummy times), by solving a linear system with a parameter (the third \
frequency). At second order, the frequency variables which are evaluated \
after integration by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["t", "1"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "329f3ada-7707-4cfe-a621-41147286de9b"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["t", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f71f3d28-1487-46fd-9265-71909161eef7"],
 " are labeled as \[Gamma] and \[Epsilon]. Consequently, the time differences \
multiplying \[Gamma] and \[Epsilon] must contain the times ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["t", 
    RowBox[{"1", " "}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c33b0174-893b-40a1-9a20-96706184a012"],
 "and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["t", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "50bda3a7-9193-47f3-9151-17272b748c30"],
 ", otherwise the integration fails. Next, the integration over (t-t\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]) is performed by solving a single linear equation, \
obtained by equating the coefficient of (t-t\[CloseCurlyQuote]) in the total \
polynomial to zero. Note that the time interval that multiplies \[Digamma]  \
must contain t and/or t\[CloseCurlyQuote].  However, t and \
t\[CloseCurlyQuote] shall not appear together in that time interval, \
otherwise the time ordering of the corresponding Goldstone diagram becomes \
undefined (or ambiguously defined). Consequently, in the denominators of the \
energy representation, multiple \[OpenCurlyQuote]omegas\[CloseCurlyQuote] may \
appear, depending on the topology of the unoriented Goldstone diagram. \
Besides, the time interval multiplying \[Digamma]  shall never coincide with \
the one multiplying \[Gamma] or \[Epsilon], otherwise the implemented time \
sequence is ill-defined."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8883163242658205`*^9, 3.8883163554476023`*^9}, {
